","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I have not investigated, but the reporter confirmed that the problem is gone in Chrome beta:\r\nhttps:\/\/bugs.chromium.org\/p\/chromium\/issues\/detail?id=914608#c6\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-12-13T22:34:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422#issuecomment-447145409","id":447145409,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0NzE0NTQwOQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-13T22:34:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/447145409","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I looked around the repro code and realized this is not a bug. It's a policy change started from M71:\r\nhttps:\/\/developers.google.com\/web\/updates\/2018\/11\/web-audio-autoplay\r\n\r\n__The context must be activated upon user input.__ Otherwise, the context will not run thus scheduled events will not be processed. See more comments: https:\/\/bugs.chromium.org\/p\/chromium\/issues\/detail?id=914608#c13","created_at":"2018-12-14T17:27:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422#issuecomment-447394403","id":447394403,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0NzM5NDQwMw==","updated_at":"2018-12-14T17:27:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/447394403","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> The context must be activated upon user input.\r\n\r\n`three.js` creates its internal audio context lazily when `AudioContext.getContext()` is executed for the first time. This usually happens when users create an instance of `AudioListener`, `Audio` or `PositionalAudio`. As long as this object creation is performed after a user interaction, things should work fine, right?\r\n\r\nIn our demos, we are doing the initialization after a button click. For example here:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webaudio_timing.html\r\n\r\nCan you confirm that this code demonstrates a valid approach for creating the audio context and using the Web Audio API?","created_at":"2018-12-14T18:00:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422#issuecomment-447403798","id":447403798,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0NzQwMzc5OA==","updated_at":"2018-12-14T18:00:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/447403798","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Well, the code is minified. Also when I searched keywords for \"new AudioContext\", \".resume\", or \".start\" I ended up with nothing. But I found this:\r\n\r\n```\r\naudio.play(); \/\/ play audio with perfect timing when ball hits the surface\r\n```\r\n\r\nI assume this `audio` object is some sorts of abstraction on top of AudioBufferSourceNode. But I haven't checked. This call is inside of `render()` which is not originated from the user action.\r\n\r\nPerhaps `AudioContext.getContext()` should call `resume()` if it is instantiated upon user action?\r\n\r\nOut of curiosity, what do you get out of `AudioContext.getContext()`? Does it return an `AudioContext` instance? Then you have a name conflict, no? Without reading up on the abstraction built on top of Web Audio API, it's really hard to give you a good answer.","created_at":"2018-12-14T18:28:25.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422#issuecomment-447412457","id":447412457,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0NzQxMjQ1Nw==","updated_at":"2018-12-14T18:28:25.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/447412457","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Sry, let me provide you some code snippets to illustrate the workflow:\r\n\r\nAs you can see here, when the button is clicked we execute our initialization routine of the example.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/f55b3d3b91b0f50c28523ed707baec91ddff465a\/examples\/webaudio_timing.html#L100-L101\r\n\r\nIn this `init()` function we have the following code which creates the audio listener object. It is usually  a child of the camera.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/f55b3d3b91b0f50c28523ed707baec91ddff465a\/examples\/webaudio_timing.html#L143-L144\r\n\r\nThe ctor of `AudioListener` then calls `AudioContext.getContext()` in order to have a reference to the raw audio context. \r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/f55b3d3b91b0f50c28523ed707baec91ddff465a\/src\/audio\/AudioListener.js#L11-L17\r\n\r\nSince it's the first call of `AudioContext.getContext()`  in this example, the audio context is created at that point.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/f55b3d3b91b0f50c28523ed707baec91ddff465a\/src\/audio\/AudioContext.js#L7-L19\r\n\r\n> I assume this audio object is some sorts of abstraction on top of AudioBufferSourceNode. \r\n\r\nCorrect. Objects of type `Audio` and `PositionalAudio` always have to be created with the central audio listener of the app (ctor parameter). In this way, they get access to the raw web audio context.","created_at":"2018-12-14T18:48:35.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422#issuecomment-447418335","id":447418335,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15422","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0NzQxODMzNQ==","updated_at":"2018-12-14T18:50:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/447418335","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"NONE","body":"You can try two things to see if the audio works correctly:\r\n\r\n1. Try to print out `context.state` after `AudioContext.getContext()`. You should see `running` if everything works out. If not, somehow user activation is not being delivered to the context's constructor. (and that might be a chrome bug)\r\n2. In Chrome, Go to Setting > Content Settings > Sound > Allow, try to add your page's URL. If the option 1 doesn't work whereas this forced setting works, then it confirms that this might be a bug in Chrome.","created_at":"2018-12-14T18:57:56.0